OL,3,CGranada Debate: Is it time for a
OL,4,Cvoting system change?
OL,6,FHe said: "I never thought I'd say
OL,7,Fthese words but I think it is now time
OL,8,Fto look at the voting system, when it
OL,9,Fwas a two party state if you like then
OL,10,Ffirst past the post worked, but when
OL,11,Fyou four, or five parties in some
OL,12,Fparts of the country then clearly its
OL,13,Fbroken and it actually distorts
OL,14,Fgrotesquely the results.
OL,16,F"Nigel Farage is right, I think it was
OL,17,Fjust under a million votes you needed
OL,18,Fto get to get a Reform candidate, and
OL,19,Fonly 20,000 for a Labour one elected."
