OL,3,CGranada Debate: Is it time for a
OL,4,Cvoting system change?
OL,6,FSpeaking for Labour, newly elected
OL,7,FOliver Ryan, MP for Burnley, is
OL,8,Fagainst reforming the voting system.
OL,10,FHe said: "It's important to have a
OL,11,Fconnection to a constituency and to
OL,12,Frepresent those people in Burnley and
OL,13,FPadiham that have sent me here to do a
OL,14,Fjob.
OL,16,F"Anyone who remembers the European
OL,17,Felection style will know that people
OL,18,Fgenerally didn't really see their
OL,19,FMEPs, didn't really know who they
OL,20,Fwere, it was very disconnected."
