OL,3,CGranada Debate: Is it time for a
OL,4,Cvoting system change?
OL,6,FHe added: "The two-party system, as
OL,7,Fmuch as it gets a lot of flack from
OL,8,Fdifferent smaller parties and that's
OL,9,Fkind of what they're there for, it's
OL,10,Fabout where you compromise.
OL,12,F"So if you go to the polling station
OL,13,Fand you think I might like a little
OL,14,Fbit of what Labour are saying on this,
OL,15,Fbut they're not completely perfect on
OL,16,Fthat, but I'm going to hold my nose
OL,17,Fand vote for them because I don't want
OL,18,Fthe Tories to stay - you're doing the
OL,19,Fcompromising yourself.
